 want to preserve their purchase history. What should you do?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Delete the vendor — PO history is retained separately"},{"id":"b","text":"Open the vendor detail, click the Deactivate button on the Info tab to set them as Inactive","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Remove all POs associated with the vendor, then delete the vendor record"},{"id":"d","text":"Change the vendor's payment terms to 'Suspended'"}],"explanation":"Deactivating a vendor preserves the full record including all PO history, scorecard data, and contact information. The vendor simply won't appear in active vendor lists or PO vendor dropdowns. You can reactivate them later if needed."},{"id":"vn7","text":"What payment terms options are available when creating a vendor?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Only Net 30 and Net 60"},{"id":"b","text":"Due on Receipt, Net 15, Net 30, Net 45, Net 60, and COD","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Payment terms are free-text and can be anything"},{"id":"d","text":"Payment terms are set globally in Admin and cannot vary per vendor"}],"explanation":"The Payment Terms dropdown offers standard commercial terms: Due on Receipt, Net 15, Net 30, Net 45, Net 60, and COD (plus a blank 'none' option). These terms are inherited by new POs placed with the vendor."},{"id":"vn8","text":"How does the vendor search box apply your search term?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"It filters automatically a moment after you stop typing (a short debounce); pressing Enter applies it immediately","isCorrect":true},{"id":"b","text":"Search only works on the Company Name field — other fields are ignored"},{"id":"c","text":"You must select a status filter before the search will run"},{"id":"d","text":"Nothing happens until you have typed at least 3 characters"}],"explanation":"The vendor search filters automatically on a short debounce after you stop typing; pressing Enter applies it immediately. It searches across company name, contact name, email, and phone fields